\citation{xiao2018gandiva}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Stage decomposition: each spatial policy (\textsc  {base}) paired with phase-shift (\textsc  {+ps}), and STPS's own macro-dispatch \textsc  {stps-spatial} with phase-shift added; the full scheduler is \textsc  {stps-spatial+ps}. 4 cards, mixed fingerprints, $BW_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}=\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}9\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}\times \tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}10^{5}$, $D_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}=\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}2$, 5 seeds. Phase-shift collapses NoC congestion from $\sim $0.26 to $\le 0.01$ on every spatial baseline; on full STPS the drop is 0.26\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}$\to $\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}0.16 because Stage\nobreakspace  {}A's topology- and burstiness-aware placement has already absorbed the easiest temporal slack.}}{10}{table.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:q2_phase}{{3}{10}{Stage decomposition: each spatial policy (\textsc {base}) paired with phase-shift (\textsc {+ps}), and STPS's own macro-dispatch \textsc {stps-spatial} with phase-shift added; the full scheduler is \textsc {stps-spatial+ps}. 4 cards, mixed fingerprints, $BW_{\max }\!=\!9\!\times \!10^{5}$, $D_{\max }\!=\!2$, 5 seeds. Phase-shift collapses NoC congestion from $\sim $0.26 to $\le 0.01$ on every spatial baseline; on full STPS the drop is 0.26\,$\to $\,0.16 because Stage~A's topology- and burstiness-aware placement has already absorbed the easiest temporal slack}{table.3}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Stage\nobreakspace  {}A under a utilisation sweep (4 cards $\times $ 512 cores, Poisson, mixed fingerprints, 5 seeds). At low load BestFit/DRF dominate because empty-capacity signals overwhelm topology signals; from 0.85 onward Stage\nobreakspace  {}A converges into the leader band and at 0.95 all schedulers cluster in a 0.20--0.23 strip --- the regime where physical saturation removes spatial degrees of freedom.}}{10}{table.4}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:q1_util}{{4}{10}{Stage~A under a utilisation sweep (4 cards $\times $ 512 cores, Poisson, mixed fingerprints, 5 seeds). At low load BestFit/DRF dominate because empty-capacity signals overwhelm topology signals; from 0.85 onward Stage~A converges into the leader band and at 0.95 all schedulers cluster in a 0.20--0.23 strip --- the regime where physical saturation removes spatial degrees of freedom}{table.4}{}}
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{Fingerprint predictability determines whether Stage\nobreakspace  {}A wins.}{10}{section*.18}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {5}{\ignorespaces Stage\nobreakspace  {}A under a fingerprint-composition sweep (4 cards, Poisson, 70\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}\% utilisation). Baselines ignore fingerprints and post the same card-CV everywhere; only Stage\nobreakspace  {}A reads the workload's topology and therefore changes. At 100\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}\% steady-flat Stage\nobreakspace  {}A delivers the lowest card-CV of any scheduler --- the design intent. The advantage erodes as the workload becomes more bursty, because $H\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}=\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}64$ forecast cannot resolve next-tick peaks.}}{10}{table.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:q1_mix}{{5}{10}{Stage~A under a fingerprint-composition sweep (4 cards, Poisson, 70\,\% utilisation). Baselines ignore fingerprints and post the same card-CV everywhere; only Stage~A reads the workload's topology and therefore changes. At 100\,\% steady-flat Stage~A delivers the lowest card-CV of any scheduler --- the design intent. The advantage erodes as the workload becomes more bursty, because $H\!=\!64$ forecast cannot resolve next-tick peaks}{table.5}{}}
\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {6}{\ignorespaces How each metric responds as the phase-shift budget $D_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}$ grows from 2 to 16 (light regime C, 4 cards, mixed fingerprints, 5 seeds). Congestion is a switch, not a knob; load-balance improves with diminishing returns and saturates near $D_{\qopname  \relax m{max}}\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}=\tmspace  -\thinmuskip {.1667em}8$; tail delay and throughput cost grow monotonically with the offset budget. The three columns pull in opposite directions, which is what fixes a small default.}}{11}{table.6}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:q2_dmax}{{6}{11}{How each metric responds as the phase-shift budget $D_{\max }$ grows from 2 to 16 (light regime C, 4 cards, mixed fingerprints, 5 seeds). Congestion is a switch, not a knob; load-balance improves with diminishing returns and saturates near $D_{\max }\!=\!8$; tail delay and throughput cost grow monotonically with the offset budget. The three columns pull in opposite directions, which is what fixes a small default}{table.6}{}}
